# Project setup overview

Welcome to **{{ project_name_slug }}**. This page ties together the three platform-specific
guides, explains the Conda environments that ship with the template, and walks
through the one-time commands that put Snakemake under your fingertips.

## 1 Prerequisites (all platforms)

| Tool          | Notes                                                        |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **git**       | With support for authenticated access to github.             |
| **conda**     | we suggest miniforge with the libmamba solver                |
| **Snakemake** | Installed via the *{{ package_name }}-py312-workflow* env    |
| **VS Code**   | The recommended (and only supported) development environment |

See documentation for installing on [Windows](windows.md) and [SLURM](slurm.md) platforms.

## 2 Conda environments used by this template

The file `template/workflow/config/config.yaml.jinja` enumerates every Conda
environment the workflow may touch. As shipped, the list is:

| Environment file                                       | Created by                                                                                         | Purpose                                                                                                                                   |
| ------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `workflow/envs/{{ package-name }}-py312-workflow.yaml` | template. committed to git.                                                                        | Tiny *driver* env able to run Snakemake itself                                                                                            |
| `workflow/envs/{{ package-name }}-py312-tox.yaml`      | template. committed to git.                                                                        | Minimal env to run the tox test-matrix                                                                                                    |
| `workflow/envs/pyproject2conda/*.yaml`                 | `snakemake pyproject2conda`                                                                        | Conda environment files produced from the dependencies listed in `pyrpoject.toml`. These do not install the `{{ package_name }}` package. |
| `workflow/envs/localized/*.yaml`                       | `snakemake conda_localize`. This command must be run before running any other `snakemake` command. | Copy of every `pyrpoject2conda/*.yaml` but with the {{ package_name }} installed using the full path specific to this machine.            |
| `workflow/envs/*/*.yaml`                               | -                                                                                                  | See `workflow/schemas/config.schema.yaml` for a description of the created environments.                                                  |

> **Tip:** `snakemake --summary` will tell you which rules depend on which envs.

## 3 Core setup steps (once per machine)

Execute the following *after* completing **one** of the OS-specific guides
([Linux](linux.md), [Windows + WSL](windows.md) or [SLURM](slurm.md)).


1. Clone the freshly-generated repository

```bash
git clone {{ repository_url }}.git && cd {{ project_slug }}
```

2. Build and activate the full developer environment

```bash
mamba env create -f envs/environment.yml
conda activate {{ project_slug }}
```

3. Install pre-commit hooks

```bash
pre-commit install
pre-commit run --all-files
```

4. Localize the conda environment files with the full-path to the package

```bash
snakemake conda_localize --cores 1
```
